OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 17 Jun to Fri 26 JunFA
OL,6,Fchangeable period is likely through
OL,7,Fthe middle and latter part of next
OL,8,Fweek with outbreaks of occasionally
OL,9,Fheavy rain focused across the north
OL,10,Fand especially west, some of which
OL,11,Fcould spread to parts of the south and
OL,12,Fsoutheast at times. Some strong winds
OL,13,Fmay accompany this, mainly around
OL,14,Fcoasts in the north and west. Through
OL,15,Fnext weekend and into the following
OL,16,Fweek, high pressure will probably
OL,17,Fbecome more dominant with conditions
OL,18,Fturning more widely dry and settled.
OL,19,FTemperatures are likely to be above
OL,20,Fnormal for most parts, and across the
OL,21,Fsoutheast in particular it could be
OL,22,Fvery warm or hot at times, especially
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fnext weekend.
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1781277116
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 27 Jun to Sat 11 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure is expected to lie close
OL,7,Fto the UK at the start of this period,
OL,8,Fbringing largely settled and dry
OL,9,Fconditions. Temperatures will likely
OL,10,Fbe above normal, with the potential
OL,11,Ffor hot conditions to develop,
OL,12,Fespecially in the south. Into July,
OL,13,Fthe influence of high pressure may
OL,14,Fweaken or shift more to the north or
OL,15,Fwest of the UK, bringing an increasing
OL,16,Fchance of more unsettled weather and
OL,17,Fthunderstorms, especially in the
OL,18,Fsouth. Temperatures will probably ease
OL,19,Fback closer to normal too, although
OL,20,Fsome warm and humid spells are still
OL,21,Fpossible at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
